parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Engine Control Unit (ECU) can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine will not go above 1000 RPM
the vehicle loses power
and the ECU fails to function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to be unable to see important information such as speed, fuel level, and warning lights, leading to accidents or safety risks.
symptoms: The instrument cluster lights do not come on
the speedometer
tachometer
and fuel gauge do not work
and the dashboard lights flicker or go out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hood lift cylinder can cause the hood to close unexpectedly, potentially causing injury or obstructing the driver's view.
symptoms: The hood does not stay open
the hood closes unexpectedly
the hood requires a makeshift solution (e.g.
paper clamp) to stay open
the hood stays open longer on warm days than on cold days.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the instrument panel can cause a loss of vital information, such as speed, fuel level, and engine performance, which can affect vehicle safety and operation.
symptoms: The instrument panel is inoperative
the panel takes an extended time to turn on (e.g.
30 minutes)
the panel may not turn on at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leakage into the trunk can cause damage to the vehicle's electrical components, carpets, and other materials, leading to costly repairs and potential safety hazards.
symptoms: Water leaks into the trunk
water damage to the trunk area
appointment made with the dealer to address the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to be unaware of critical vehicle information, such as speed and fuel level, which can lead to accidents, traffic violations, and safety risks.
symptoms: The instrument cluster goes dead intermittently
speedometer and tachometer needles do not work
fuel gauge is unresponsive
lights fail to turn on at night
inability to monitor fuel level
leading to running out of gas.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical fire under the hood can cause damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to a total loss, and poses a risk of injury or death to the occupants.
symptoms: Smoke and fire under the hood
burning smell
potential injury or death.
